If I create a group in a "Read Only, with Local Groups" directory it will be flagged as a local group. If a group with the same name is later created in LDAP then my local group will continue to shadow it - the local definition will be used, and changes won't be synchronised across from LDAP.

The distinction should clearly be indicated in the UI.

The obvious fix is to delete the local group and re-synchronise, but trying to delete that group through the Confluence UI fails with an exception in the logs. It should be possible to discard the shadow group from the UI.

